<subSubSection lastPageId="116" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="115" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="115.[701,1228,1026,1759]" lastBlockId="116.[93,620,213,1120]" lastPageId="116" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="115" pageNumber="115">
COMMENTS: When 
<bibRefCitation author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[985,1227,1176,1198]" pageId="115" pageNumber="115" pagination="435 - 454" refId="ref144671" refString="Sharpe, R. B. 1887. Notes on a collection of birds made by Mr. John Whitehead on the mountain of Kina Balu, in northern Borneo, with descriptions of new species. Ibis (5) 5: 435 - 454, pls. XIII and XIV." type="journal article" year="1887">Sharpe (1887: 452)</bibRefCitation>
described this form, Whitehead had not yet returned from Borneo, but had sent ahead to Sharpe one or 
<specimenCount box="[890,1064,1265,1287]" pageId="115" pageNumber="115" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of any form that he considered new (
<bibRefCitation author="Whitehead, J." pageId="115" pageNumber="115" refId="ref147812" refString="Whitehead, J. 1893. Exploration of Mount Kina Balu, north Borneo. London: Gurney and Jackson, 317 pp." type="book" year="1893">Whitehead, 1893: 185</bibRefCitation>
). Sharpe described only the male and gave a single measurement but no further information that would assist in its identification. After Whitehead returned from his 1888 expedition to Kinabalu, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sharpe, R. B." pageId="115" pageNumber="115" pagination="409 - 443" refId="ref144793" refString="Sharpe, R. B. 1889. On the ornithology of northern Borneo, with notes by John Whitehead. Parts 1 - 4. Ibis (6) 1: 63 - 85, 185 - 205, 265 - 283, 409 - 443." type="journal article" year="1889">Sharpe (1889: 428)</bibRefCitation>
reported specimens of this species from both 1887 and 1888 visits. Only a single specimen of this species, a male, was dated 1887. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, R. L. M. &amp; C. J. O. Harrison" box="[776,1125,1560,1582]" pageId="115" pageNumber="115" refId="ref147412" refString="Warren, R. L. M., and C. J. O. Harrison. 1971. Type-specimens of birds in the British Museum (Natural History), Vol. 2. Passerines. London: Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History), 628 pp." type="book" year="1971">Warren and Harrison (1971)</bibRefCitation>
did not report a type of this form in BMNH; and, in fact, a considerable number of Sharpe’s and Ogilvie-Grant’s types based on Whitehead specimens were retained by Whitehead and later sold to Rothschild. In addition to the Rothschild Collection label, the above speci- men bears John Whitehead’s small field label with his unique field number ‘‘966’’ and on the reverse ‘‘descr,’’ in what is probably Whitehead’s hand; it is not initialed by Sharpe. The wing measures 
<quantity box="[425,510,330,352]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
, which is approximately the 
<quantity box="[324,458,360,382]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.953" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" unit="in" value="1.95">1.95 inches</quantity>
given in the original description. It isn’t possible to be sure that AMNH 697914 was collected on 
<date pageId="116" pageNumber="116" value="1887-02-15">15 February 1887</date>
, or at 
<quantity box="[364,452,448,470]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2192" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" unit="ft" value="4000.0">4000 ft</quantity>
, which is the altitude at which Whitehead said he first met this bird (
<bibRefCitation author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[206,473,507,530]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" pagination="409 - 443" refId="ref144793" refString="Sharpe, R. B. 1889. On the ornithology of northern Borneo, with notes by John Whitehead. Parts 1 - 4. Ibis (6) 1: 63 - 85, 185 - 205, 265 - 283, 409 - 443." type="journal article" year="1889">Sharpe, 1889: 428–429</bibRefCitation>
); however, a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[258,558,536,559]" class="Aves" family="Nectariniidae" genus="Arachnothera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis box="[258,558,536,559]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="116">Arachnothera longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected on 
<date box="[231,418,566,588]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" value="1887-03-04">4 March 1887</date>
was numbered ‘‘1059,’’ indicating that no. ‘‘966’’ was collected earlier. This probable 
<typeStatus box="[480,582,626,648]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharpe" authorityYear="1887" box="[93,225,654,677]" class="Aves" family="Dicaeidae" genus="Dicaeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monticolum">
<emphasis box="[93,225,654,677]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="116">monticolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been added to the AMNH type collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="116.[93,620,213,1120]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116">
The other 
<specimenCount box="[261,381,715,737]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" type="adult">two adult</specimenCount>
specimens and an immature that 
<bibRefCitation author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[271,493,744,766]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" pagination="409 - 443" refId="ref144793" refString="Sharpe, R. B. 1889. On the ornithology of northern Borneo, with notes by John Whitehead. Parts 1 - 4. Ibis (6) 1: 63 - 85, 185 - 205, 265 - 283, 409 - 443." type="journal article" year="1889">Sharpe (1889: 428)</bibRefCitation>
listed also came to AMNH: AMNH 697915 (Whitehead no. 2368) and AMNH 697925 (2369), male and female, collected on Kinabalu on 
<date pageId="116" pageNumber="116" value="1888-04-01">1 April 1888</date>
, and AMNH 697923 (2322), a female collected on 
<date box="[358,560,892,914]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" value="1888-03-27">27 March 1888</date>
, the immature described as having the base of the bill yellowish white, a characteristic discernible even in the specimen. AMNH 697924 was collected on Kinabalu on 
<date pageId="116" pageNumber="116" value="1888-03-29">29 March 1888</date>
, but was not listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sharpe, R. B." pageId="116" pageNumber="116" pagination="409 - 443" refId="ref144793" refString="Sharpe, R. B. 1889. On the ornithology of northern Borneo, with notes by John Whitehead. Parts 1 - 4. Ibis (6) 1: 63 - 85, 185 - 205, 265 - 283, 409 - 443." type="journal article" year="1889">Sharpe (1889)</bibRefCitation>
. None of these 1888 specimens has any standing as a 
<typeStatus box="[257,310,1099,1120]" pageId="116" pageNumber="116">type</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
